{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775830987629,"sessionID":"ses_2883bc6c3ffeGLRvqmCBoCzzsE","part":{"id":"prt_d77c45f19001DsMz66E4oDpwUP","messageID":"msg_d77c44896001CF6QzdCPAa66GM","sessionID":"ses_2883bc6c3ffeGLRvqmCBoCzzsE","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_210db7c597af495ca1ad4d7e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project at /home/dsj/benchmark to understand:\n\n1. Find the pkg/router directory and understand its current structure\n2. Look for any existing JWT, auth, or authentication related code\n3. Find any existing design documents or architecture docs\n4. Look at the main project structure to understand the overall architecture\n5. Check for any existing middleware, handlers, or router configuration\n6. Look for any configuration files (go.mod, etc.) to understand dependencies\n7. Search for any existing JWT or token-related patterns in the codebase\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of:\n- The project structure overview\n- Current router implementation details\n- Any existing auth/JWT patterns\n- Key files and their purposes\n- Dependencies related to JWT/auth","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_2883b913effe2ghm8941wjufCQ (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a comprehensive understanding of the agentcube project. Here is my complete summary:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Analysis of AgentCube Project\n\n### 1. Project Overview\n\n**AgentCube** is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents. It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through session-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n**Source Location:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z`\n\n**Go Module:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n\n---\n\n### 2. Project Structure Overview\n\n```\nworkspace/\n├── go.mod                          # Go module definition (Go 1.25.0)\n├── go.sum                          # Dependency lock file\n├── design.md                       # AR-009 Router design document\n├── pkg/\n│   ├── router/                     # HTTP Router (traffic entry point)\n│   │   ├── config.go               # Server configuration\n│   │   ├── server.go               # Gin server setup, route registration, lifecycle\n│   │   ├── router.go               # Router interface & routing table\n│   │   ├── proxy.go                # Reverse proxy & request forwarding\n│   │   ├── jwt.go                  # JWTManager (RS256 token generation)\n│   │   ├── middleware.go           # Concurrency limit, logging, trace ID\n│   │   ├── session_manager.go      # Session management & sandbox creation\n│   │   ├── backend.go              # Backend health checking\n│   │   ├── loadbalancer.go         # Round-robin & least-connections LB\n│   │   ├── informer.go             # K8s CRD informer integration\n│   │   ├── health.go               # Liveness/readiness endpoints\n│   │   └── errors.go               # Custom error types\n│   ├── store/                      # Session storage layer\n│   │   ├── store.go                # Store interface (Redis/Valkey)\n│   │   ├── store_redis.go          # Redis implementation\n│   │   ├── store_valkey.go         # Valkey implementation\n│   │   ├── codec.go                # Serialization\n│   │   └── singleton.go            # Singleton pattern\n│   ├── workloadmanager/            # Control plane for sandbox lifecycle\n│   │   ├── handler/\n│   │   │   ├── sandbox_create.go   # Sandbox creation with auth\n│   │   │   ├── sandbox_delete.go   # Sandbox deletion with auth\n│   │   │   ├── sandbox_lifecycle.go\n│   │   │   ├── models.go           # Request/Response types\n│   │   │   └── constants.go\n│   │   ├── reconciler/             # K8s controller reconciler\n│   │   └── response/               # HTTP response helpers\n│   ├── apis/runtime/v1alpha1/      # CRD type definitions\n│   │   ├── agent_type.go\n│   │   ├── codeinterpreter_types.go\n│   │   ├── shared_types.go         # AuthModeType, ProtocolType\n│   │   └── groupversion_info.go\n│   └── common/types/\n│       └── types.go                # Shared constants (Kind types)\n├── client-go/                      # Generated K8s typed client\n├── specs/                          # Design specifications (at benchmark root)\n│   ├── session-routing/design.md\n│   ├── sandbox-orchestration/design.md\n│   └── project.md\n└── delta-spec.md                   # OpenSpec delta specification\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Current Router Implementation Details\n\n**Location:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/`\n\nThe router is the HTTP traffic entry point (port 8080) with 12 Go source files:\n\n#### 3.1 Server (`server.go`)\n- Uses **Gin** as the HTTP framework\n- Contains: `gin.Engine`, `http.Server`, `SessionManager`, `store.Store`, `http.Transport`, `JWTManager`\n- Supports HTTP/2 via h2c (plaintext upgrade)\n- Optional TLS support\n- Graceful shutdown with signal handling\n\n#### 3.2 Route Registration (`server.go:registerRoutes()`)\n\n| Method | Path | Middleware | Handler |\n|--------|------|------------|---------|\n| GET | `/health/live` | none | `handleHealthLive` |\n| GET | `/health/ready` | none | `handleHealthReady` |\n| GET, POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | Logger, Recovery, ConcurrencyLimit | `handleAgentInvoke` |\n| GET, POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | Logger, Recovery, ConcurrencyLimit | `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` |\n\n#### 3.3 Proxy (`proxy.go`)\n- Uses `httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy` for reverse proxying\n- Resolves sandbox entry points from session store\n- Injects `X-Forwarded-*` headers\n- Adds JWT `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header for Sandbox/SandboxClaim kinds\n- Sets `x-agentcube-session-id` response header\n- Error mapping: connection refused -> 502, timeout -> 504\n\n#### 3.4 Session Manager (`session_manager.go`)\n- Reads `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable (required)\n- Looks up sandbox by session ID from store, or creates new sandbox via WorkloadManager\n- Uses K8s service account token for auth to WorkloadManager\n\n#### 3.5 Load Balancer (`loadbalancer.go`)\n- `RoundRobinBalancer`: Thread-safe round-robin selection\n- `LeastConnectionsBalancer`: Atomic counter-based least-connections\n\n#### 3.6 Backend Health Checker (`backend.go`)\n- Configurable interval, consecutive failure/success thresholds\n- Default health check: HTTP GET `/health`\n\n---\n\n### 4. Existing Auth/JWT Patterns\n\n#### 4.1 JWT Implementation (`jwt.go`)\n\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/jwt.go`\n\n```go\ntype JWTManager struct {\n    privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey\n    publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n    clientset  kubernetes.Interface\n}\n```\n\n**Key characteristics:**\n- **Algorithm:** RS256 (RSA Signature with SHA-256)\n- **Key Size:** 2048-bit RSA\n- **Token Expiration:** 5 minutes\n- **Issuer:** `\"agentcube-router\"`\n- **Base Claims:** `exp`, `iat`, `iss`\n- **Custom Claims:** Merged from caller (e.g., `session_id`)\n\n**Key Management:**\n- Generates ephemeral RSA key pair on startup\n- Attempts to store/load keys from K8s Secret `picod-router-identity` in namespace (from `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env var, default `default`)\n- Falls back to ephemeral keys if not running in-cluster\n- Secret contains `private.pem` (PKCS1) and `public.pem` (PKIX)\n\n**JWT Usage Flow:**\n1. Router generates JWT with `session_id` claim when forwarding to sandbox\n2. JWT is set as `Authorization: Bearer <token>` on proxied request\n3. Only applied for `Sandbox` and `SandboxClaim` kinds (not for direct invocations)\n4. Sandbox pods (with PicoD) receive the public key via `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var for verification\n\n#### 4.2 WorkloadManager Auth (`sandbox_create.go`, `sandbox_delete.go`)\n\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox_create.go`\n\n- `EnableAuth` flag controls whether auth is enforced\n- Extracts `Authorization` header, strips `Bearer ` prefix\n- Uses `TokenCache` or `UserClientFactory` to create per-user K8s dynamic clients\n- Returns 401 if token is missing when auth is enabled\n\n#### 4.3 AuthMode Types (`shared_types.go`)\n\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go`\n\n```go\ntype AuthModeType string\nconst (\n    AuthModePicoD AuthModeType = \"picod\"\n    AuthModeNone  AuthModeType = \"none\"\n)\n```\n\n- `AuthModePicoD`: Sandbox uses PicoD daemon for JWT verification\n- `AuthModeNone`: No authentication on sandbox\n\n#### 4.4 PicoD Auth Injection (`sandbox_create.go:injectPicodAuthEnv`)\n- Reads public key from K8s Secret `picod-router-identity`\n- Injects `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var into sandbox pod's first container\n\n---\n\n### 5. Key Files and Their Purposes\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `pkg/router/server.go` | Main server: Gin setup, route registration, TLS/h2c, lifecycle |\n| `pkg/router/jwt.go` | JWT RS256 token generation, K8s Secret key management |\n| `pkg/router/proxy.go` | Reverse proxy, request forwarding, JWT injection, error handling |\n| `pkg/router/session_manager.go` | Session resolution, sandbox creation via WorkloadManager |\n| `pkg/router/middleware.go` | Concurrency limiting (429), request logging, trace ID |\n| `pkg/router/config.go` | Server configuration struct with defaults |\n| `pkg/router/backend.go` | Backend health checking with configurable thresholds |\n| `pkg/router/loadbalancer.go` | Round-robin and least-connections load balancing |\n| `pkg/router/router.go` | Basic Router interface and route table (map-based) |\n| `pkg/router/informer.go` | K8s CRD informer for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter |\n| `pkg/router/health.go` | Liveness/readiness health endpoints |\n| `pkg/router/errors.go` | Custom error types (SessionNotFound, SandboxTemplateNotFound, SessionTerminated) |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox_create.go` | Sandbox creation with auth, CRD building, PicoD auth injection |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox_delete.go` | Sandbox deletion with auth |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/models.go` | Request/Response types (SandboxInfo, EntryPoint, etc.) |\n| `pkg/store/store.go` | Store interface for session/sandbox persistence |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` | AuthModeType, ProtocolType, TargetPort |\n| `design.md` | AR-009 Router design document (comprehensive) |\n| `specs/session-routing/design.md` | Session routing specification |\n| `specs/project.md` | Project context and architecture overview |\n\n---\n\n### 6. Dependencies Related to JWT/Auth\n\n**From `go.mod`:**\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | v5.2.1 | JWT RS256 signing/verification |\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | v1.10.0 | HTTP framework, middleware |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.34.1 | K8s API client (Secret management, in-cluster config) |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | v0.34.1 | K8s errors, metav1 types |\n| `k8s.io/api` | v0.34.1 | K8s core types (Secret, Pod) |\n| `golang.org/x/net` | v0.51.0 | HTTP/2 support (h2c) |\n| `github.com/google/uuid` | v1.6.0 | Session ID generation |\n\n---\n\n### 7. Design Documents\n\n| Document | Location | Content |\n|----------|----------|---------|\n| Router Design | `design.md` | AR-009: Full router architecture, data structures, API contracts, error handling, test strategy |\n| Session Routing Spec | `specs/session-routing/design.md` | Session routing design with Config, Server, JWT, proxy details |\n| Project Context | `specs/project.md` | Architecture overview, tech stack, conventions |\n| Implementation Plan | `PLAN.md` | AR-023 through AR-033 mapping (integrations, CLI, SDK, Helm, CI/CD) |\n\n---\n\n### 8. Summary of Auth Flow\n\n```\nClient Request\n  -> Router (port 8080)\n     -> Extracts x-agentcube-session-id header\n     -> Looks up sandbox in Redis/Valkey store\n     -> If no session: calls WorkloadManager to create sandbox\n     -> Forwards request to sandbox pod via reverse proxy\n        -> Generates JWT (RS256, 5min expiry, session_id claim)\n        -> Sets Authorization: Bearer <JWT> on proxied request\n     -> Sandbox (PicoD) verifies JWT using public key from env var\n```\n\nThe current JWT implementation is focused on **router-to-sandbox authentication** (the router signs requests, sandboxes verify them). There is no existing JWT-based client-to-router authentication pattern -- the router does not currently validate incoming JWT tokens from clients.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_2883b913effe2ghm8941wjufCQ","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775830855357,"end":1775830987627}}}}
